{
  "stem": "20035.4",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I have to say that every-- that march of going from the camp to the railroad station, we went through one part of town.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Until today, if somebody is telling you that they didn't know about it, somehow I asked the question that if you see 10,000 or 6,000 or 8,000-- I don't know how many at the same time-- marched with stripes and basically, feeble looking or--",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--funny-looking people go through, don't you ask the questions, who are they?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Are they prisoners?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What do you mean a prisoner?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Prisoners for what?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, they didn't know about concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Don't tell me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Braunschweig ended, basically, on a-- on an interesting note of-- started to have air raids in March, twice a day, 10 o'clock, 4 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like a routine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Till one day, finally-- by the way, we were not allowed to go to any shelter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to dig a ditch outside of the factory, in between the railroad station and the factory.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a long ditch where we had to-- that was our shelter, or whatever you want to call it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Both end of the ditch there was a SS guard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Finally, after a week or 10 days of continuous air raids, finally the day come when the Allies-- the planes came in and in the morning the--",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
